        "paragraph_index": 3,
        "text": "### Chemistry insight\n\nThe PbCl⁺ formation constant is one of the most extensively studied metal–halide equilibria, reflecting lead's environmental and geochemical importance. The sheer number of citations (spanning 1930–1994) underscores how critical accurate Pb–Cl speciation data is for fields ranging from electrochemistry to marine geochemistry. The large body of independent measurements also helps constrain recommended \"best\" values at standard conditions (25 °C, zero ionic strength), where log β₁ ≈ 1.6 is widely accepted.\n\n*Source: NIST Standard Reference Database 46 (SRD-46)*",
